<subSubSection id="03A785B8200DF6392092690514F6526D" pageId="114" pageNumber="115" type="reference_group">
<paragraph id="4B65C5FD4CAB25CF006E6B784D1BDB34" pageId="114" pageNumber="115">
<taxonomicName id="6F1A0DF804E00E1F7FD6E44424562B3E" authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia vulcanicola" order="Myrtales" pageId="114" pageNumber="115" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="vulcanicola">Conostegia vulcanicola</taxonomicName>
Donn. Sm., Bot. Gaz. 42: 294. 1906. Type: Costa Rica. Forets de 
<normalizedToken id="F94DC97DED9E684B790EDBDCFC556E3B" originalValue="l’Achiote">l'Achiote</normalizedToken>
, 
<normalizedToken id="0427A1F2E96B0A08C07B0AAD4739C2F6" originalValue="volcán">volcan</normalizedToken>
de 
<normalizedToken id="07CEBED32320477C96E32BD97A46F638" originalValue="Poás">Poas</normalizedToken>
, 2200 m, November 1896, Tonduz 10840 (lectotype: NY!, designated here; isolectotypes: BR[2]!, US!). Other syntypes: Costa Rica. Forets de 
<normalizedToken id="D57D52FDB25C4182C7F64C123B2A09F6" originalValue="l’Achiote">l'Achiote</normalizedToken>
, 
<normalizedToken id="470B254901C0ADE8CC7001485668F8FA" originalValue="volcán">volcan</normalizedToken>
de 
<normalizedToken id="DFE03A67F12E38A8604BC81020323625" originalValue="Póas">Poas</normalizedToken>
, 2100 m elevation, A. Tonduz 10836 (BR, M, US [
<bibRefCitation id="A796DFD89216FD9C8603022E388717C7" author="Schnell, CE" journalOrPublisher="Harvard University" pageId="243" pageNumber="244" refId="B77" refString="Schnell, CE, 1996. The Genus Conostegia (Melastomataceae). Harvard University" title="The Genus Conostegia (Melastomataceae)" year="1996">Schnell (1996)</bibRefCitation>
notes that &quot;this number is mixed with 
<taxonomicName id="C5A4A8DF3E715F6A09625E1E47888244" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Miconia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Miconia tonduzii" order="Myrtales" pageId="114" pageNumber="115" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="tonduzii">Miconia tonduzii</taxonomicName>
Cogn. at BR and US; at CR it includes no 
<taxonomicName id="33A5355C5ABC22F63D8F1C31AE03B97A" authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia" order="Myrtales" pageId="114" pageNumber="115" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">Conostegia</taxonomicName>
material]), 10840 (BR [2], NY, US)&quot;.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="BF4C96F0E0F95BBE91F8DCCECCBFF8C3" lastPageId="115" lastPageNumber="116" pageId="114" pageNumber="115" type="description">
<paragraph id="46B4A02065BB988E080F69AD4EF97755" pageId="114" pageNumber="115">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B7DCBC82BB8216BEA452C63C38E516F2" lastPageId="115" lastPageNumber="116" pageId="114" pageNumber="115">
Shrubs or small trees 3 to 5 m tall with flattened stems that become terete with age and are densely puberulent with sessile stellate trichomes; the nodal line present yet slight. Leaves of a pair equal to somewhat unequal in length. Petioles 1-3.8 cm. Leaf blades 5-15 
<normalizedToken id="EA9127DB0CB8E3A55ED74BB23E500D3A" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
2-7.1 cm, 5-plinerved, with the innermost pair of primary veins diverging from ca. 1 cm from the blade base the midvein in opposite to subopposite fashion, elliptic-ovate to elliptic, the base acute, the apex acute to acuminate,the margin 
<pageBreakToken id="7FE5BC28C0EB32AE5DED2675C5F39C69" pageId="115" pageNumber="116" start="start">entire</pageBreakToken>
or ciliate, the adaxial and abaxial foliar surfaces covered with small stellate hairs. Inflorescence a terminal panicle 3-10 cm, accessory branches apparently absent, the rachis with small stellate hairs, linear, the bracteoles to 3 mm, deciduous. Pedicel 5-20 mm. Flowers 5-6 merous, calyptrate. Floral buds 4-7 
<normalizedToken id="3442DA09FE0BC5FCD22A7398947D160F" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
2-3.5 mm, oblong-pyriform, the base rounded, the apex acute to short apiculate, slightly constricted below the calyptra. Petals 5-7 mm long, white or pinkish, broadly obovate, spreading, glabrous. Stamens 10-12 (-13), 4-5 mm long, possibly slightly bilateral, the filaments ca. 2.5 mm, white, anthers ca. 2 mm long, linear oblong, yellow, the pore ca. 0.2 mm, terminal. Ovary 4-5-locular, inferior, apically glabrous and forming a low collar around the style. Style 3-5 mm, bending below the stigma, apparently no vertical or horizontal distance between the anthers and the stigma, truncate or subcapitate. Berries 5-7 
<normalizedToken id="9174BDFCEBE2E0895B1484278231BB24" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
5-7 mm, purple-black. Seeds ca. 0.7 mm long, obliquely pyramidal, the testa smooth.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="09135E22BE3162326E94F698374B279A" lastPageId="116" lastPageNumber="117" pageId="115" pageNumber="116" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="BE8187EDDC1B397775F45E4C5BAADC49" pageId="115" pageNumber="116">Distribution</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C0CC74A4792A6C8274D8086E0B43FD55" pageId="115" pageNumber="116">
(Fig. 
<figureCitation id="955928AC8B0E300E92F13F0663BEF0B1" captionStart="Figure 113" captionStartId="F113" captionText="Figure 113. Distribution of Conostegia vulcanicola." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.67.6703.figure113" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/96471" pageId="115" pageNumber="116">113</figureCitation>
). Costa Rica and reported from Panama by 
<bibRefCitation id="DE3285FD38A51DFB6A302E0B32B537F5" author="Schnell, CE" journalOrPublisher="Harvard University" pageId="243" pageNumber="244" refId="B77" refString="Schnell, CE, 1996. The Genus Conostegia (Melastomataceae). Harvard University" title="The Genus Conostegia (Melastomataceae)" year="1996">Schnell (1996)</bibRefCitation>
, 1550-2400 m in elevation.
</paragraph>
<caption id="94FBEF44C255C95705CEF1B1161482CA" ID-Zenodo-Dep="973868" doi="10.3897/phytokeys.67.6703.figure113" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/96471" pageId="115" pageNumber="116" start="Figure 113" startId="F113">
<paragraph id="349F143D5F066A9523230AE0A7576667" pageId="115" pageNumber="116">
<emphasis id="667555D24166D90042E3851C536A1065" bold="true" pageId="115" pageNumber="116">Figure 113.</emphasis>
Distribution of 
<taxonomicName id="2515C7F52D6F6C386D05F30B5470E6A4" authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia vulcanicola" order="Myrtales" pageId="115" pageNumber="116" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="vulcanicola">
<emphasis id="0D9F017481765018A165BFD0ED412FF9" italics="true" pageId="115" pageNumber="116">Conostegia vulcanicola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="22B17F325F866CB3AB08C2DB7B2613DB" pageId="116" pageNumber="117">
<pageBreakToken id="6141ACD1655188B90EF7C70030A88252" pageId="116" pageNumber="117" start="start">Considering</pageBreakToken>
the lengthy discussions provided by 
<bibRefCitation id="E4343C92BE17305A4043C68E73120250" author="Schnell, CE" journalOrPublisher="Harvard University" pageId="243" pageNumber="244" refId="B77" refString="Schnell, CE, 1996. The Genus Conostegia (Melastomataceae). Harvard University" title="The Genus Conostegia (Melastomataceae)" year="1996">Schnell (1996)</bibRefCitation>
in problematic species, it is interesting he did not discuss anything under 
<taxonomicName id="AD5112E5BFF9EE83F179DC56AD30D4E3" authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia vulcanicola" order="Myrtales" pageId="116" pageNumber="117" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="vulcanicola">
<emphasis id="63E137BB50BD7B9E3D368DAF2B096B97" italics="true" pageId="116" pageNumber="117">Conostegia vulcanicola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, although he did mention that 
<taxonomicName id="8B314B86AFBA5F201CF6308CE064455E" authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia micrantha" order="Myrtales" pageId="116" pageNumber="117" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="micrantha">
<emphasis id="E3D9AA10B93DEBB91407670BAD279731" italics="true" pageId="116" pageNumber="117">Conostegia micrantha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="B1F936A83DFB94630EEF10CF469E919F" authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia vulcanicola" order="Myrtales" pageId="116" pageNumber="117" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="vulcanicola">
<emphasis id="E1AAA3401C788779E3CD03FC993F80E3" italics="true" pageId="116" pageNumber="117">Conostegia vulcanicola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were probably derived from 
<taxonomicName id="FA7BD0BAC7B8A2B9EE53E6662839BDF4" authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia montana" order="Myrtales" pageId="116" pageNumber="117" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="montana">
<emphasis id="6CF34C76DD55297613B1EA617176EE56" italics="true" pageId="116" pageNumber="117">Conostegia montana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. I have gone to several volcanoes in Costa Rica looking for 
<taxonomicName id="6CE462582C360482C4E7DA769EABA9A3" authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia vulcanicola" order="Myrtales" pageId="116" pageNumber="117" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="vulcanicola">
<emphasis id="76870A7E670EE07031C7E144380E8FF4" italics="true" pageId="116" pageNumber="117">Conostegia vulcanicola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and I found populations that resemble the type specimen except mostly for the reddish hairs on the newest vegetative growth. In general, these specimens also resemble and I have annotated as 
<taxonomicName id="8DF04A936A8B766B2D96BAEC482C16E1" authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia montana" order="Myrtales" pageId="116" pageNumber="117" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="montana">
<emphasis id="B164B0CEE470425FB1190A8218C92BA2" italics="true" pageId="116" pageNumber="117">Conostegia montana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The isolectotype of 
<taxonomicName id="2D1BB638281908C493C29C67745237D0" authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia vulcanicola" order="Myrtales" pageId="116" pageNumber="117" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="vulcanicola">
<emphasis id="D4A10191C022549618BE197B6B4AAC78" italics="true" pageId="116" pageNumber="117">Conostegia vulcanicola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was previously identified as 
<taxonomicName id="33D1C41FA015E5DE8397B91F49BB4075" authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia montana" order="Myrtales" pageId="116" pageNumber="117" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="montana">
<emphasis id="BE66FAAD6DE288D723EA26B48E76977E" italics="true" pageId="116" pageNumber="117">Conostegia montana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
apparently by A. Tonduz and another specimen identified by H. A. Gleason as 
<taxonomicName id="F5A396717C084D638B5F0CD464A77DB6" authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia montana" order="Myrtales" pageId="116" pageNumber="117" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="montana">
<emphasis id="F7D76FD3FCC84F705302A0891CD96563" italics="true" pageId="116" pageNumber="117">Conostegia montana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was annotated as 
<taxonomicName id="8178D0F4155044B22DCF2DB76EA0714F" authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia vulcanicola" order="Myrtales" pageId="116" pageNumber="117" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="vulcanicola">
<emphasis id="1A0B7185F28CBE526DAAD8D0FA03413A" italics="true" pageId="116" pageNumber="117">Conostegia vulcanicola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by Schnell. The main differences between the two taxa at this time are the indument mentioned above as well as leaf venation. 
<taxonomicName id="73BE04549FA07C36655EE2502F1972D1" authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia vulcanicola" order="Myrtales" pageId="116" pageNumber="117" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="vulcanicola">
<emphasis id="93FB0120EFC2CD3075DCAF88B8F2AC30" italics="true" pageId="116" pageNumber="117">Conostegia vulcanicola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
tends to have plinerved leaves whereas 
<taxonomicName id="C99D866EBC88E9C23895F46B95115599" authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia montana" order="Myrtales" pageId="116" pageNumber="117" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="montana">
<emphasis id="517691E89D20A6958BF6DA82DB6B8649" italics="true" pageId="116" pageNumber="117">Conostegia montana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
lack the reddish indument and usually has nerved leaves. Further investigation into this species complex is needed.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
